3Occurrences for Indiana are not strictly limited to divorce. Rather, estimates reflect “domestic relations” (DR) cases, which include marital dissolution, legal separation, and establishment of child support agreements. Unfortunately, it was not possible to separate marital dissolution from other types of DR cases.
****Number of divorces are greater than 0 but less than 5. Exact number unknown.

Glass, J. & Levchak, P. (2010). County-Level Marriage & Divorce Rates, 2000. Original Data Collection. Bowling Green, OH: National Center for Family & Marriage Research. Retrieved from http://ncfmr.bgsu.edu/page81181.html.
